will find information about:   General Career Resources  Research a Company or an Industry  General Career Advice  Skills Development  Salary Information       General Career Resources      What Can I Do With This Major? Learn about possible career options that connect to particular majors.     My Next Move Learn about possible career options that connect to particular majors.    Occupational Outlook Handbook Research education requirements, earnings, job prospects, what employees do on the job, and working conditions for occupations/careers.    Vault Career Insider Research employers, industries and career subjects. Note:  Users must create a login account.    O*Net Online Research occupational descriptions and data based on data from the U.S. Department of Labor.    Career One Stop Research occupational descriptions and data based on data from the U.S. Department of Labor.    Jobscan Jobscan is a tool that gives job seekers an instant analysis of how well their resume is tailored for a particular job and how it can be even better optimized for an ATS.    Kanopy Access free, on-demand video library containing variety of video materials including career "day in the life" videos.         Research a Company or an Industry      Company or Industry Research a company or industry using recommended resources.  Company or Industry Look up news about companies and/or industries using recommended resources.   General Career Advice      The Muse Access this website for wide range of career topics and advisement.    The Balance Careers Access this website for career advice on job searching, resume writing, salary negotiations, and other career planning topics.        Skills Development      Lynda.com Lynda is now LinkedIn Learning. Get access to 1,200+ online courses to build skills including career development. Access available for FREE with UIC login.    UIC Career Services Career Planning Guide Use the online career guide developed by UIC Career Services containing job search tips, sample resumes and cover letters, and career advice.    UIC Career Readiness eLearning Modules Access 5 short online modules on the common career topics, now available on YouTube :   Mastering the Elevator Pitch From Intern to Full-Time Employee: Making the Most of Your Internship Workplace Communication: Overcoming Barriers to Thrive in Your Internship or Entry-level Job Your First Year on the Job: Strategies for Success in Your New Position Navigating a Job Fair You may also access these modules on UIC Blackboard - Career Readiness 101 module.    Career Podcasts Use CareerBuilder.com's list of recommended career podcasts featuring career experts and recruiters discussing career and job search topics.    LinkedIn Learning Get access to 1,200+ online courses to build skills including career development. Access available for FREE with UIC login.    UIC Career Services YouTube Videos  Watch these videos created by UIC Career Services outlining tips and advice on career topics.        Salary Information      NACE Salary Calculator Research salaries based on college, location, & other factors based on data sourced from federal databases.    Job Star Central Find other salary websites through this reference site.    Glassdoor.com Access online resource summarizing companies as well as submitted company reviews (by current/prior employees), salaries, job listings, and more.    Salary.com A catalogue of free courses addressing key elements of the compensation agenda.    Payscale A comprehensive resource for prepping for your next salary negotiation.    LinkedIn Salary Explore how salaries vary by industry, company size, education level and field of study.         Students    Back to main content           Career Programs and Events    Career Advising    Career Exploration     Career Education Resources      Resumes, CVs, and Cover Letters    Interviews    Jobs    Internships    Networking    Student Success Stories     Graduate Outcomes    Journey to Success Nomin